    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>A beam of brilliant light flashes out from your hand in a 5-foot-wide, 60-foot-long &amp;Reference[line]{line}. Each creature in the &amp;Reference[line]{line} must make a &amp;Reference[con]{Constitution} saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes 6d8 &amp;Reference[radiant]{radiant} damage and is &amp;Reference[blinded]{blinded} until your next turn. On a successful save, it takes half as much damage and isn't &amp;Reference[blinded]{blinded} by this spell. &amp;Reference[undead]{Undead} and oozes have disadvantage on this saving throw.</p>\n<p>You can create a new &amp;Reference[line]{line} of radiance as your action on any turn until the spell ends.</p>\n<p>For the duration, a mote of brilliant radiance shines in your hand. It sheds bright light in a 30-foot radius and dim light for an additional 30 feet. This light is sunlight.</p>\n</div>",
